"The user starts with View 1 at the Overview level to see sales patterns across product categories and time segments. Category selection triggers updates in Views 2-5. View 2 (Exploration) reveals price-quantity relationships, View 3 (Exploration) compares revenue metrics, View 4 (Insight) shows inventory-sales alignment, and View 5 (Insight) detects pricing anomalies. Interactions flow from category selection to all subordinate views, enabling progressive refinement from patterns to actionable insights."